campsites.name: LillyPad Campground
campsites.description: A small campground with a craft brewery on the Cumberland Plateau, adjacent to the Obed Wild and Scenic River National Park. We serve home-grown beer. You can also eat here at The Sauced Frog . There is nothing like a good craft beer, delicious food in your belly, a cozy campfire, and some impromptu strumming under the stars.

campsites.name: Blue Heron Campground
campsites.description: Blue Heron Campground is a rustic and spacious campground, situated on the Kentucky side of The Big South Fork National River and Recreation Area--a vast and scenic expanse of land that offers visitors countless recreational activities.

campsites.name: Tennessee Wall Campground
campsites.description: Minimal campsite along the road with few amenities. Near a popular rock climbing destination

campsites.name: Jackson Falls
campsites.description: Peaceful dirt road with pull offs for car camping, dispersed tent spots in the woods, and a small parking lot for extra cars.

campsites.name: Miguels Pizza
campsites.description: Miguel's Pizza offers cheap and unique camping with some of the best rock climbing in the Eastern U.S. In your downtime, enjoy good food, a basketball court, and other fun games. Enjoy some amazing pizza and a refreshing adult beverage all within walking distance to your tent!

campsites.name: North River Campground
campsites.description: Looking for a beautiful place to camp near the river? Look no further! This small campground has 11 sites, a scenic river, and more wilderness then Steve Irwin could shake a stick at! for those who love Rafting, Kayaking, Hiking, And Fly Fishing, You have now found your own paradise!

campsites.name: Looking Glass Rock
campsites.description: A Distinct 3,969-ft. monolith with a rounded granite face, a popular hiking & climbing destination. Camping is located throughout the wilderness here and is classified as "dispersed". there are also many pull-offs you can car camp in.

campsites.name: Indian Creek
campsites.description:
It's a nice campground. It's quiet and the atmosphere is really nice. They have a couple of pit toilets and a couple of places with running water. There are no showers. Some very large picnic tables are scattered throughout the campground. It is a great place for tent camping but would not be very good for RVs. Lots of rock climbing and atv trails in the area as well! very beautiful! 

** A High Clearance 4X4 Vehicle is recommended!!!

campsites.name: Land of the Arches Campground
campsites.description: LOTA is a great campground with bathrooms, hot showers, Free Wifi a huge indoor recreation area with table tennis, air hockey, and tables to sit and chat. Tent Camping is $8 per person per night. Indoor camping (bring your own bedroll is $10 per person per night). For indoor camping, you must reserve online. there are also rooms with beds available to rent and even a tiny cottage!
